The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during a visit to Tampa General Hospital in Florida. Pence thanks Tampa General and the University of South Florida for their efforts in healthcare and assures the people of Florida that the government will provide whatever they need during the pandemic. He commends Florida for their testing efforts and promises to continue expanding testing statewide. Pence also emphasizes the importance of wearing masks and practicing social distancing, especially for young people who may not be at high risk but can still infect vulnerable individuals. He praises Florida's focus on protecting the elderly and discusses ways to support their efforts. Pence concludes by expressing unity and confidence in the country's ability to overcome the pandemic and rebuild the economy.